<HEADLINE>
<P>
3 SOUGHT IN HOLDUP OF MARKET IN FILLMORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities were searching Sunday for three men who held up a Fillmore market 
and fled with an undetermined amount of cash. 
</P>
<P>
Ventura County Sheriff's Lt. Wendy Kemp said two men entered Handy Market at 
801 A St. about 7:20 p.m. As one of the men walked behind the counter, the 
other pulled a gun on the cashier. The man behind the counter grabbed money 
from the cash register, and the two fled in a car driven by a third man who had 
waited outside. 
</P>
<P>
No one was injured. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061890-0007 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 235233 </DOCID>
