<P>
* The Community Noise Equivalent Level (CNEL), derived by averaging noise 
readings, is the state-mandated measure of airport noise. In January, 1986, the 
state tightened the CNEL standard for acceptable community noise from 70 
decibels to 65 decibels. The 65 CNEL zone encloses the area in which all the 
average readings are 65 decibels or higher. 
</P>
