<P>
Oil Minister Gholamreza Aghazadeh said Iran's oil production capacity will rise 
more than 25% to 4.5 million barrels a day in two years. He said Iran is 
spending hundreds of millions of dollars to repair damage to the industry from 
the 1980-88 Iran-Iraq War. Oil brings in 90% of Iran's foreign currency 
revenues. 
