named Sharon, a former defense minister, and Eitan, chief of staff during the 
Lebanon invasion, to the 11-man ministerial Defense Committee. Sharon, a leader 
of the conservative Likud Party, also was named chairman of a Cabinet committee 
overseeing the immigration of Soviet Jews. 
