<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 3.7-magnitude earthquake rattled the San Bernardino-Riverside area late 
Saturday night, but there were no reports of injuries, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The 11:08 p.m. temblor was centered six miles southeast of San Bernardino, said 
Doug Smith, spokesman for the Caltech Seismology Laboratory in Pasadena. 
</P>
</TEXT>
