<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By James S. Granelli and Tom McQueeney 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WE'RE NO. 1: Orange County is "the Mecca of mail fraud," says postal inspector 
Kacy McClelland (D6). "When you've got your scheme perfected, here's the place 
you put it in motion." . . . Most crooks either rent space in Newport Beach or 
get a mail drop so they can assume a Newport address. . . . "They are selling a 
dream, the California promise: 'You can be rich quick and live here like we do 
in Newport -- the good life,' " he says. James S. Granelli and Tom McQueeney 
</P>
</TEXT>
