</P>
<P>
JAIL INMATE ESCAPES FROM LOCAL HOSPITAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Orange County Jail inmate was being sought Sunday after she escaped from a 
local hospital, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
JoAnne Gonzalez, 24, escaped at 10:05 p.m. Saturday from Western Medical Center 
in Santa Ana, where she had been taken for examination, Sheriff's Lt. Harold 
Schaffroth said. 
</P>
<P>
Gonzalez had been in custody since early Friday morning on warrants for 
prostitution, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Schaffroth, who did not know which law enforcement department had placed 
Gonzalez under arrest, said the woman had been an inmate at the jail when she 
was taken to the hospital for examination. The reason for her visit to the 
hospital was confidential, he said. 
</P>
<P>
However, at the hospital, "when the deputy's attention was distracted, she 
slipped her handcuffs and got away," Schaffroth said. "Investigators have been 
assigned to locate Ms. Gonzalez, and she is not considered dangerous to 
others," he said. 
</P>
<P>
Gonzalez, who was last seen wearing an Orange County Jail-issue blue jumpsuit, 
was described as being about 5 feet, 2 inches tall, weighing 140 pounds and 
having black hair and brown eyes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
