<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN CLEMENTE CYCLIST RANKED 3RD IN NATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kenny Adams of San Clemente became the third-ranked professional cyclist in the 
United States Sunday, placing sixth overall in the Core State Pro Championships 
at Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
Adams' teammate, Kurt Stockton of Santa Barbara, placed third overall, becoming 
the top-ranked American cyclist. 
</P>
<P>
Adams and Stockton compete for the Anaheim-based American Commerce National Pro 
Cycling team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
