<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND; 
</P>
<P>
BATTERIES BLAMED IN DISNEY FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pair of storage batteries that either shorted out or overheated sparked a 
fire that filled a Disney film production building in Burbank with thick smoke 
today but caused no injuries and little damage, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
A Walt Disney Co. spokesman said the only people in the building when the fire 
broke out about 5:45 a.m. were security personnel. The fire was doused shortly 
after 6 a.m. 
</P>
</TEXT>
