<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
SOVIET PILOT REQUESTS ASYLUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANKARA, Turkey 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Soviet pilot landed a small plane on a beach on the Black Sea coast today and 
requested political asylum, a government official said. 
</P>
<P>
Tass news agency reported in Moscow that an AN-2 plane was hijacked in Izmail, 
near the Ukrainian port of Odessa. 
</P>
<P>
The Turkish official said the pilot was alone in the 12-seat Soviet passenger 
plane when it landed near Kumcagiz village in Kocaeli province at 1:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
There are no airports in the province, and the plane landed on a beach known as 
Kefken, the official said. He said the Soviets immediately asked Turkey to 
return the plane and the pilot. 
</P>
<P>
The semiofficial Anatolia news agency identified the pilot as Valeri Yurevic, 
29. He was reportedly taken to a police station for questioning. 
</P>
<P>
Tass said the pilot had resigned several months ago from his job with an Odessa 
air crew. It did not give further details. 
</P>
</TEXT>
