<P>
U.S. JOCKEY COUNCILOR FRACTURES HER SKULL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MEDICINE HAT, Alberta 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Laura Councilor, a first-year jockey, was in serious but stable 
condition today at Calgary Foothills Hospital where she was flown after an 
accident at the Medicine Hat Exhibition &amp; Stampede Grounds. 
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old rider from Phoenix suffered a fractured skull Sunday when she 
was thrown from her mount, Arms Walk Out, and kicked in the head by another 
horse as it tried to jump over her. 
</P>
<P>
"They said that her skull is fractured in two places, one on each side," said 
Councilor's husband, Don. "It could have been a lot worse, that's for sure. She 
can move her arms and legs." 
</P>
</TEXT>
